## Domain-Level Permissions with Builder Role

Context: OntoBricks had a flat, app-wide permission model (admin/editor/viewer/none).
This change introduces a new "builder" role and per-domain permission overrides.
Builders can do everything editors can, plus trigger digital twin builds. Editors
can no longer build digital twins. Domain-level permissions let admins restrict
(but not elevate) a user's app-level role on a per-domain basis.

Changes:

1. `src/back/objects/registry/permissions.py` — added `ROLE_BUILDER` constant,
   `ROLE_HIERARCHY` dict, `role_level()` and `min_role()` helpers; added domain
   permission file I/O (`load_domain_permissions`, `save_domain_permissions`);
   added `get_domain_role()` with effective = min(app, domain) logic; added
   domain-level CRUD (`list_domain_entries`, `add_or_update_domain_entry`,
   `remove_domain_entry`, `clear_domain_perm_cache`).

2. `src/back/objects/registry/__init__.py` — re-exported `ROLE_BUILDER`,
   `ROLE_HIERARCHY`, `role_level`, and `min_role`.

3. `src/shared/fastapi/main.py` — updated `PermissionMiddleware` to resolve
   both `user_role` (app-level) and `user_domain_role` (effective domain role);
   renamed `_resolve_role` to `_resolve_roles`; added `builder` awareness;
   added `/settings/domain-permissions` to admin-only prefixes.

4. `src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py` — added builder/admin authorization
   check on `POST /dtwin/sync/start` (digital twin build endpoint).

5. `src/back/services/settings.py` — updated role validation to accept
   "builder"; added domain-permission orchestration functions
   (`list_domain_permissions_result`, `add_domain_permission_result`,
   `delete_domain_permission_result`).

6. `src/api/routers/internal/settings.py` — added three new endpoints:
   `GET/POST /settings/domain-permissions/{domain_name}` and
   `DELETE /settings/domain-permissions/{domain_name}/{principal}`.

7. `src/front/templates/settings.html` — added "Builder" role option to the
   app-level permission modal dropdown; added Domain-Level Permissions
   sub-section with domain selector, per-domain permission table, and
   Add Domain Permission modal.

8. `src/front/static/config/js/permissions.js` — added "Builder" option to
   the inline role-change select; added full domain-permission management
   UI logic (load, change, add, delete).

9. `src/front/fastapi/dependencies.py` — added `get_user_domain_role` Jinja2
   global function.

10. `src/front/templates/partials/dtwin/_query_sync.html` — Build button is
    now conditionally rendered: shown for builder/admin, disabled with lock
