## Fix: Principal Search Now Queries App Permissions Instead of SCIM

### Context

The "Search Workspace" feature in the Add Permission modal never
returned users.  The root cause: `search_workspace_principals` was
calling the SCIM `/preview/scim/v2/Users` endpoint to search all
workspace users, but the Databricks App service principal typically
lacks SCIM read permissions, so the call silently failed and returned
an empty list.

The correct behaviour is to search among users and groups that already
have access to the Databricks App (via the App Permissions API), which
is the same data shown by `list_app_principals`.

### Changes

1. `src/back/services/settings.py` — `search_workspace_principals()`
   - Replaced SCIM `DatabricksClient.search_users/search_groups` calls
     with `permission_service.list_app_principals()` + client-side
     case-insensitive contains filter on email/display_name.
   - Removed now-unused `DatabricksClient` import from the function.

2. `tests/test_settings_domain_permissions.py` — added `TestSearchWorkspacePrincipals`
   - Filters by email, by display name, case-insensitive match.
   - Group search filtering.
   - No-match returns empty list.

### Modified files

- src/back/services/settings.py
- tests/test_settings_domain_permissions.py

Tests: 1265 passed, 45 skipped.

