## Extract graph DB abstraction layer: new `back.core.graphdb` package

### Context

The graph DB engine (LadybugDB) was coupled to the triple store package
(`back.core.triplestore`), sharing the same ABC (`TripleStoreBackend`) and
factory (`TripleStoreFactory`). The triple store (Delta views in Unity
Catalog) and the graph DB are two separate concerns: the triple store is the
permanent storage layer; the graph DB is a local/embedded engine for Cypher
queries, traversal, and reasoning. This refactoring separates them so that
the graph DB engine can be swapped in the future.

### Changes

1. Created `src/back/core/graphdb/` package with:
   - `GraphDBBackend.py` — abstract base extending `TripleStoreBackend` with
     capability flags (`supports_cypher`, `supports_graph_model`,
     `query_dialect`), connection management, schema introspection, UC Volume
     sync methods, and `get_query_translator()` for reasoning engines.
   - `GraphDBFactory.py` — factory with `engine` parameter (default
     `"ladybug"`) and `get_graphdb()` convenience function.
   - `__init__.py` — exports `GraphDBBackend`, `GraphDBFactory`,
     `get_graphdb`, `GRAPHDB_AVAILABLE`.

2. Moved `src/back/core/triplestore/ladybugdb/` to
   `src/back/core/graphdb/ladybugdb/`.

3. `LadybugBase` now extends `GraphDBBackend` instead of `TripleStoreBackend`.
   Implements all graph-specific methods: `get_connection()`, `get_node_table()`,
   `get_graph_schema()`, `sync_to_remote()`, `sync_from_remote()`,
   `local_path()`, `remote_archive_path()`, `get_query_translator()`.

4. `LadybugGraphStore` overrides `supports_graph_model` and
   `get_query_translator()` to return `SWRLCypherTranslator` when graph
   schema is active.

5. `TripleStoreFactory` simplified: only handles Delta (`backend="view"`);
   `backend="graph"` delegates to `GraphDBFactory.get_graphdb()`.

6. All internal imports within the `ladybugdb/` package updated from
   `back.core.triplestore.ladybugdb` to `back.core.graphdb.ladybugdb`.

7. Updated `src/.coding_rules.md` section 10.2 to document the new
   `graphdb/` package alongside `triplestore/`.

### Modified files

- src/back/core/graphdb/__init__.py (new)
- src/back/core/graphdb/GraphDBBackend.py (new)
- src/back/core/graphdb/GraphDBFactory.py (new)
- src/back/core/graphdb/ladybugdb/__init__.py (moved + updated)
- src/back/core/graphdb/ladybugdb/LadybugBase.py (moved + updated)
- src/back/core/graphdb/ladybugdb/LadybugFlatStore.py (moved + updated)
