Refactor infrastructure modules to raise `ValidationError`, `NotFoundError`,
`InfrastructureError`, and `ConflictError` instead of returning `success: False`
dicts, so FastAPI global handlers return consistent HTTP errors.

### Changes

1. `src/back/core/w3c/sparql/SparqlTranslator.py` — SPARQL→SQL validation failures
   raise `ValidationError` instead of `{success: False, message: ...}`.
2. `src/back/core/sqlwizard/SQLWizardService.py` — `generate_sql` raises
   `ValidationError` / `InfrastructureError`; re-raises `OntoBricksError`.
3. `src/back/core/helpers/DatabricksHelpers.py` — `require_serving_llm` returns
   `(host, token, endpoint)` or raises `ValidationError`.
4. `src/back/core/industry/fibo/FiboImportService.py`,
   `src/back/core/industry/cdisc/CdiscImportService.py`,
   `src/back/core/industry/iof/IofImportService.py` — invalid selection raises
   `ValidationError`; zero modules fetched raises `InfrastructureError`.
5. `src/api/routers/internal/tasks.py` — missing task → `NotFoundError`; cancel
   failure → `ConflictError`.
6. `src/back/fastapi/graphql_routes.py` — GraphQL error payloads use
   `_graphql_safe_error_message` (no raw `str(exception)` for clients).
7. `src/api/routers/internal/ontology.py` — callers updated for new
   `require_serving_llm` signature.
8. `src/back/objects/ontology/ontology.py` — industry import: removed dead
   `result["success"]` branch; import `OntoBricksError` for existing re-raise.
9. `src/api/routers/domains.py` — Spark SQL route relies on translator raises;
   re-raise `OntoBricksError` before generic handler.
10. `src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py` — background build catches
    `OntoBricksError` from `translate_sparql_to_spark` for task failure.
11. `src/back/objects/registry/scheduler.py` — removed redundant post-translate
    success check (errors raise).
12. Tests: `tests/test_sparql_service.py`, `tests/test_sql_wizard.py`,
    `tests/test_external_api.py` aligned with exceptions.

