### Context

Reduce repeated credential resolution + UC client construction, centralize default
ontology host string, reuse triplestore RDF URI constants, and deduplicate
SPARQL translator local-name helpers.

### Changes

1. **6b — ``make_volume_file_service``** — ``src/back/core/helpers/DatabricksHelpers.py``
   adds ``make_volume_file_service(domain, settings=None)`` (optional settings
   falls back to cached ``get_settings()``). Re-exported from
   ``src/back/core/helpers/__init__.py``. Call sites that used
   ``get_databricks_host_and_token`` + ``VolumeFileService(host=host, token=token)``
   in internal routers now use the factory:
   ``src/api/routers/internal/_helpers.py``,
   ``src/api/routers/internal/domain.py``,
   ``src/api/routers/internal/ontology.py`` (OWL volume list/load only),
   ``src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py`` (reload-from-registry uses
   ``uc.is_configured()``). Left unchanged: ``home.py`` (manual host/token),
   ``dtwin`` build thread (credentials from ``get_databricks_credentials``), and
   other packages.

2. **6c — URI local names** — ``src/back/objects/digitaltwin/digitaltwin.py`` uses
   ``extract_local_name`` for class/property local-name extraction instead of
   ad-hoc ``split('#')`` / ``split('/')``.

3. **6d — ``DEFAULT_BASE_URI``** — ``DatabricksHelpers.resolve_default_base_uri``
   and ``src/api/routers/internal/settings.py`` ``save_base_uri`` default use
   ``shared.config.constants.DEFAULT_BASE_URI`` (``.rstrip('/')`` where the prior
   literal had no trailing slash).

4. **6e — RDF_TYPE / RDFS_LABEL** — ``src/back/core/graph_analysis/CommunityDetector.py``
   imports ``RDF_TYPE`` / ``RDFS_LABEL`` from ``back.core.triplestore.constants``.
   ``src/back/core/w3c/shacl/SHACLService.py`` ``_extract_violations`` uses
   ``URIRef(RDF_TYPE)`` instead of a shadowing local string.

5. **6g — SparqlTranslator** — ``src/back/core/w3c/sparql/SparqlTranslator.py`` adds
   ``_predicate_local_name_key`` and removes duplicate nested ``get_local_name``
   definitions.

6. **6f — SWRL / rule Cypher (deferred)** — Reasoning engines still assemble Cypher
   in place per engine; a shared builder would need a agreed contract for
   node/rel shapes and parameter binding across SWRL, decision tables, and
   variants. No refactor in this pass.

